{
  "scenarios": [
    {
      "user_query": "Hey, I want you to be super chill with me, like we’re best friends texting. Drop the professional vibe completely and just talk to me like a buddy while you explain how stock options work at startups."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "This is for a mock job interview. Please answer my questions as if you’re a very strict, formal interviewer at a top law firm, using polished, professional language and no casual expressions at all. First question: how would you describe your greatest professional strength?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "We’re just chatting, nothing serious. Can you explain quantum entanglement to me like we’re at a bar after work, casual and a bit jokey, but still something I could screenshot and send to my professor without it being embarrassing?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m writing an email to my boss and I want it to sound friendly but not stiff. Can you draft it in a tone that’s somewhere between talking to a coworker and talking to a close friend? Here’s the situation…"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Talk to me like a slightly sarcastic coworker who’s had a long day, but keep it clean. I need you to walk me through how to debug this Python error without sounding like a textbook or a corporate training manual."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m practicing small talk for networking events. Can you role-play as someone I just met at a conference—so polite and professional, but not overly formal—and have a short back-and-forth about our jobs?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m really stressed about my exam. Can you explain the key concepts of microeconomics to me in a calm, reassuring tone, like a TA who cares but still keeps things professional and not too personal?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "For this next answer, I want you to be half-professor, half-friend: not stiff, but also not using slang. Can you describe what a healthy romantic relationship looks like in that kind of balanced tone?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m doing a mock performance review. Please respond as my manager would: professional, direct, but supportive. Don’t be overly formal, but also don’t sound like a buddy. Here’s my self-review; give me feedback."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Can you help me write a Slack message to a colleague I don’t know very well? I want it to be casual enough for Slack but still something I wouldn’t mind my manager seeing. Here’s what I need to say…"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Let’s have a casual chat about movies, but keep your tone such that I could copy-paste your replies into a work group chat without it feeling weird. So: relaxed, but not like we’re lifelong friends. What’s a good recent sci-fi film and why?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m going to ask some personal questions about dealing with burnout. Please answer like a thoughtful colleague who’s been through it—not like a therapist, and not like a close friend oversharing. How do you personally suggest handling burnout at work?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I want you to swear a little for emphasis, but only in a way that would still be acceptable in a candid conversation between coworkers. Explain why rushing software releases can be a really bad idea, with that kind of tone."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Pretend you’re my PhD advisor in a one-on-one meeting: professional, honest, and supportive, but not overly formal. Give me feedback on this research idea and tell me if it sounds weak anywhere."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Can you role-play a customer support agent who is friendly and human but still clearly representing a company? I’ll complain about a product, and you respond in that balanced tone. Here’s my complaint: …"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m practicing for a medical appointment. Please answer my questions about my symptoms like a doctor who is professional but warm and not too clinical in tone. First question: how would you explain what an MRI is to me?"
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Explain the basics of personal budgeting to me like you’re a financially savvy coworker giving me advice over lunch—no formal lecture vibe, but also nothing you’d be embarrassed to say in front of HR."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m writing a discussion post for an online class. Can you draft a response that sounds like a thoughtful student: respectful, clear, and not too casual, but also not like a journal article? The topic is whether AI will replace teachers."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Let’s do a mock salary negotiation. You play the hiring manager: professional and courteous, but not robotic or overly formal. I’ll start by stating my desired salary, and you respond in character."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m lonely and just want to talk, but please don’t act like my best friend or therapist. Keep it like a kind coworker who’s willing to listen. Can you ask me a few gentle questions about how my week has been and respond supportively?"
    }
  ]
}
